# Extended Scope 4 — Persistent Memory

## Roles (MEMORY 1)

Travel Hub has four user roles: **Editor**, **Companion**, **Follower** (was Shared-View Follower), and the trip creator (always Editor). Roles are stored in the **TripMembers** SharePoint list. Role enforcement uses `useCurrentUserRole` hook and `RoleGate` component.

## Financial visibility (MEMORY 2)

Financial fields (amounts, budget cards, day totals, payment status, booking references) are **never rendered** for Companion or Follower roles. They are removed from the DOM — not hidden with CSS.

## Mobile shell (MEMORY 3)

Three touch-related shells: **phone** and **iPad portrait** use `src/components/mobile/`; **iPad landscape** uses `src/components/ipad/IpadLandscapePlaceholder` until Phase B. `useShellMode()` controls routing; `useMobileMode()` is true for phone + iPad portrait only. Desktop components are never conditionally modified for mobile — mobile has its own components.

## User identity (MEMORY 4)

**UserEmail** is the primary user identity field in all data models. SharePoint user IDs may exist alongside but email is authoritative. This supports future non-SharePoint storage backends.

## Data access (MEMORY 5)

Travel Hub will eventually support self-hosted storage (Dropbox, Google Drive, OneDrive). All data access must go through **ITravelHubDataService**. No SharePoint-specific types, URLs, or query syntax may appear outside service implementation files.

## Schema safety (MEMORY 6)

All column additions to existing SharePoint lists are **append-only**. Check before create. Never delete, rename, or modify existing columns or lists. This protects live trip data.

## Shopping list (MEMORY 7)

The shopping list is already built. **OwnerEmail** column needs to be added to it. Include it in MobileListsView alongside the packing list.

## ES4 build order

Implement tasks ES4-1 through ES4-14 in order (see `docs/Travel_Hub_Cursor_Brief_ES4.docx`). Do not skip ahead to UI before ES4-3 (roles hook) is in place.

## Constraints (carry forward)

- Desktop `TripWorkspace` tree unchanged for mobile work — mobile is a sibling branch
- CSS tokens from `src/styles/global.css` only; category colours via `th-cat-{slug}` classes
- No external icon libraries; inline SVG only
- No modal dialogs — inline expand or slide-in panels only
- `npm run build` must pass after every task; commit and push after each task
